-- Safeway posts higher profit
-- 
-- Thu Jul 17, 2008 9:14am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/17/us-safeway-results-idUSWNAB110220080717

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Safeway Inc ( SWY.N ) on Thursday reported higher second-quarter profit as its sales rose and the grocer said it reduced costs. 

 The company, which operates stores under the Safeway, Vons, and Dominick's names, said net income rose to $234.3 million, or 53 cents per share, from $218.2 million, or 49 cents per share, a year earlier. (Reporting by  Nicole Maestri , editing by Gerald E. McCormick)